<HEADLINE>
<P>
'CAN WE GO HOME AGAIN?' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dennis McDougal's story ("Lynwood: Downhill on the Freeway," Part I, Aug. 20) 
was timely, interesting and certainly pointed out the major changes occurring 
in our region. 
</P>
<P>
Although he focused on Lynwood, the former All-American city, other areas have 
also undergone major changes. Overbuilding and clogged streets have all 
contributed to an erosion of the quality of life. 
</P>
<P>
I hope we will see more stories from The Times on changes in our cities and 
areas. 
</P>
<P>
Can we go home again? 
</P>
<P>
CLIFF DEKTAR 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
