<HEADLINE>
<P>
'CAN WE GO HOME AGAIN?' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last year, Lynwood commissioned Hintz &amp; Balvin Communications to create a 
video history of the city so that youngsters and newcomers could appreciate 
where they are living. In the process, we got to know Lynwood as a city of 
people who are friendly and care about their city. 
</P>
<P>
The camera crew created curiosity and people on the street were terribly 
pleased to be the focus of a positive piece on their area. The video gathered 
together Lynwood old-timers and newcomers in a project that they could all be 
proud of -- The City of Lynwood. 
</P>
<P>
We concluded that Lynwood seems to have a special sort of strength and staying 
power. It lives strongly in people's happy memories of its past but even more 
strongly in the current residents' determination to create there a new 
All-American City. 
</P>
<P>
BARBARA BOYER WALTER 
</P>
<P>
Hintz &amp; Balvin 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
