<TEXT>
<P>
The campaign to replace the late Claude Pepper in Congress wound down with a 
poll by WSCV-TV in Miami showing a virtual dead heat between Republican Ileana 
Ros-Lehtinen and Democrat Gerald F. Richman. If she wins today's special 
election to fill the 18th Congressional District seat held for 27 years by 
Pepper, Ros-Lehtinen, a state senator, would become the first Cuban-American 
voted into Congress. In the survey of 301 likely voters, Richman, a Miami Beach 
lawyer, received 47% of the vote, while Ros-Lehtinen had 45% and 8% were 
undecided. The poll carried a margin of error of 5 percentage points. Among 
black and Jewish voters, Richman's support neared 80%. Among white non-Latino 
voters, he enjoyed a 2-1 edge. Ros-Lehtinen drew support from 86% of Latino 
voters. 
