<TEXT>
<P>
A former Newport Beach resident has donated $110,000 toward building a 
permanent facility for the Women's Opportunity Center on the UC Irvine campus. 
</P>
<P>
Donna Shannon O'Bryan, who now lives in St. Helena in Napa County, donated the 
money for construction and equipment for a 4,000-square-foot building for the 
nonprofit organization, which has been providing career and personal guidance 
to women on and off campus since 1970. 
</P>
