<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: L.A. TO CLAIM LAND FOR PACOIMA SENIOR CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Board of Recreation and Park Commissioners on Monday approved the beginning 
of eminent domain proceedings to acquire land for the future Pacoima Senior 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
The two-acre parcel, northwest of Glenoaks and Van Nuys boulevards, has been 
valued at $675,000. It is near major bus routes and freeways. But the owners 
have not responded to many contacts by city parks staff, causing the city to 
initiate measures to claim the land through eminent domain. 
</P>
<P>
The center will not be built for several years, but money for land acquisition 
was included in the 1988-89 budget. 
