<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: SIERRACIN CORP. SAYS PROFIT FELL 29% IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sierracin Corp. in Sylmar said its second-quarter profit fell 29% from a year 
earlier, to $370,000 from $521,000. 
</P>
<P>
The maker of cockpit windows and other aerospace products said its revenue was 
virtually flat: $20.4 million in the latest quarter, which ended June 30, 
compared with $20.3 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Sierracin blamed the lower earnings on operating cost overruns, higher costs 
for materials, and greater provisions for excess and obsolete inventories. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of 1989, Sierracin's profit fell 11% to $845,000 from 
$951,000, and its revenue edged up to $40.9 million from $39.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
