<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: OLSON INDUSTRIES LOSES $914,730 IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Olson Industries, a Sherman Oaks plastics-packaging concern, reported a 
second-quarter loss of $914,730, compared with a loss of $1.04 million a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The loss came despite an increase in sales in the quarter that ended June 30, 
to $17.9 million from $16 million. Olson, as it has in recent quarters, blamed 
the loss mostly on higher prices for resins, the main raw material used in its 
packaging goods. 
</P>
<P>
Olson's principal unit, Dolco Packaging Corp., is operating under Chapter 11 of 
the U. S. Bankruptcy Code, whereby it is protected from creditors' lawsuits 
while working out a plan to restructure its finances. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of 1989, Olson lost $1.58 million, compared with a loss of 
$1.46 million a year earlier. Six-month sales rose to $37 million from $33.6 
million. 
</P>
