</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corrections officials have given subway gunman Bernhard Goetz two extra weeks 
in jail for failing to return a disposable razor, a violation of jailhouse 
rules, according to a published report today. 
</P>
<P>
The Daily News said Goetz refused to return the razor because he wanted to have 
one that only he would use. 
</P>
<P>
Goetz, 41, has said he believed prison officials gave him used razors that may 
infect him with the deadly AIDS virus. Prison officials maintain that all 
inmates get a new razor blade each time they shave. 
</P>
<P>
Goetz was scheduled to be released Sept. 6, but now is slated to be freed Sept. 
20, the newspaper said. 
</P>
