IRAN PARLIAMENT OKS NEW CABINET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iran's Parliament today approved all 22 nominations to President Hashemi 
Rafsanjani's new Cabinet, the country's official news agency reported. 
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Republic News Agency, monitored in Nicosia, described the vote of 
confidence by the 270-member Majlis as "unprecedented" since some members of 
all previous Cabinet slates had been rejected in the past. 
</P>
<P>
The vote came after Rafsanjani got a last-minute boost for his proposed Cabinet 
today from radical Parliament Speaker Mehdi Karrubi. 
</P>
<P>
"I see Mr. Rafsanjani's Cabinet as a successful one and one that supports the 
deprived . . . and whose members have worked hard for the revolution," Karrubi 
was quoted as saying by IRNA. 
</P>
