<DATELINE>
<P>
HENDERSONVILLE, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Boatman, longtime director of the "Hee Haw" television show and lighting 
consultant to four Presidents, was killed when a pistol accidentally discharged 
in his garage, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Boatman, 59, was found Monday lying in a pool of blood in the garage of his 
home. Authorities said a .22-caliber gun discharged when Boatman apparently 
pulled out a drawer too far and it fell. The gun was in the drawer. 
</P>
<P>
Besides directing "Hee Haw," Boatman worked as lighting consultant for 
Presidents Richard M. Nixon, Gerald R. Ford, Jimmy Carter and Ronald Reagan. 
</P>
<P>
Boatman was lighting director for "Hee Haw" from 1970 to 1972 when he became 
director. 
