<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
17 NOMINATED FOR WOMEN'S TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gold-medalist swimmer Janet Evans and jockey Julie Krone are among the nominees 
for the Women's Sports Foundation 1989 Amateur and Professional Sportswoman of 
the Year awards. 
</P>
<P>
Evans and eight other nominees, including gold-medalist pentathlete Florence 
Griffith-Joyner, are up for the amateur honor, won last year by 
Griffith-Joyner's sister-in-law, Jackie Joyner-Kersee. 
</P>
<P>
Joining Krone as nominees for the professional award are tennis star Steffi 
Graf and golfer Betsy King. 
</P>
<P>
The 17 athletes nominated for both awards have collectively earned five world 
championships and four Olympic gold medals and hold 32 major professional 
championship titles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
