<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
DEBUS DRUGS HEARING SET SEPT. 30 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Athletics Congress announced today that a hearing for former Los Angeles 
Track Club Coach Chuck DeBus has been scheduled for Sept. 30 in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
DeBus, 44, of Santa Monica has been under investigation by the congress for 
allegedly dispensing performance-enhancing substances to athletes. 
</P>
<P>
DeBus also coached track at UCLA and Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
The hearing had originally been scheduled for July 11, but the National 
Athletics Board of Review agreed to postpone the hearing five days before that 
date. William Hickman, a Seattle attorney who will chair the hearing panel, 
said there will be no further continuances. 
</P>
<P>
DeBus faces permanent expulsion from track if the panel decides against him. 
</P>
<P>
The Indianapolis-based Athletics Congress is the governing body for U.S. track 
and field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Chuck DeBus 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
