<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
HERNANDEZ TO MISS REST OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Detroit Tigers pitcher Guillermo Hernandez will miss the last weeks of the 
season because of a muscle tear in his elbow that could require surgery. The 
injury, where the forearm muscles meet the elbow, has limited Hernandez to 
pitching only eight times in the last 2 1/2 months. The Tigers' team doctor, 
Clarence Livingood, said Monday that Hernandez will be evaluated in two weeks 
to see if surgery is needed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
